11. nobis, a very doubtful line. Fistula is a conjectura] emendation for filia: with either nobis must be the dative, and quam tu supplied after fortius. Prof. Conington supposed that fistula, if the right reading, must mean the ‘windpipe‚’ in which case fortius would be used absolutely—very nearly as a positive degree. The emendation suggested by Aurelianus, given in Schneidewin, edition 1, “non nobis least seems to give a much better sense than the text. Friedlander would read ‘nobis ilia fortius loquentur.’ This has the advantage of being nearest to the MSS. reading.
